cal concepts still apply, or must we invent a new framework for this mutable medium? To answer these fundamental questions, the contributors to this provocative collection examine diverse case studies, including up-to-date scholarship on the current television zeitgeist, nostalgic programming on broadcast television, YouTube, and public television art programming of the 1980s. As a whole, these essays challenge the supposed crisis in television in the light of its burgeoning development.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aTelevision broadcasting. 0aTelevision. 7aART / General.2bisacsh1 aBouman, Margot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDhoest, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrancisco, Juan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayward, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermes, Joke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeilbach, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLozano, Gutiérrez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwaab, Herbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStauff, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeurlings, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeurlings, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUricchio, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, Mimi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade Valck, Marijke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade Valck, Marijke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators